narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I bet that a lot of the people reading this are doing Spanish L3 for the language requirement (as I did). I find language really boring and it is easily the subject I dislike the most. Taking Spanish 130 with Sebastin really helped negate this constant want to sleep in class. If you can, take the class with Sebastin.
Quite a bit of work. Do the homework in advance, it helps
Highly recommendable for anyone looking to fulfill the language requirement or for improving one's Spanish.
It is a reasonable intermediate class if you are interested in continuing Spanish/fulfilling language requirement.
Only took this bc it's a graduation requirement, but good as could be
I think the Spanish 130 02 class was enjoyable and helped my Spanish speaking a lot. I think I would recommend it with Sebastin because he is very high-energy and connected with his students.
